-[cheering continues]

120
00:05:08.434 --> 00:05:10.602
-[whooping]
-[upbeat music playing]

121
00:05:10.686 --> 00:05:11.895
[confetti pops]

122
00:05:13.897 --> 00:05:15.733
[laughs]

123
00:05:24.867 --> 00:05:26.744
-[Eva] Hi. honey.
-Uh. just one second.

124
00:05:26.827 --> 00:05:28.370
I'm almost done learning about women

125
00:05:28.454 --> 00:05:29.997
who can't experience intimacy.

126
00:05:30.080 --> 00:05:31.498
[Eva] Oh.

127
00:05:31.582 --> 00:05:32.750
Uh. Elle.

128
00:05:32.833 --> 00:05:35.711
We have something important
we want to talk to you about.

129
00:05:35.794 --> 00:05:37.337
Oh. God.

130
00:05:37.421 --> 00:05:39.423
[sighs] Is this about Marlena?

131
00:05:39.506 --> 00:05:40.966
-[laughs softly]
-Wh... [sighs]

132
00:05:41.050 --> 00:05:44.428
-Which one's Marlena?
-S... It's Days of Our Lives.

133
00:05:44.511 --> 00:05:46.430
-Oh.
-She's been possessed by pure evil.

134
00:05:46.513 --> 00:05:48.932
so John performed an exorcism on her.

135
00:05:49.016 --> 00:05:51.060
but then she went into
cardiac arrest and died.

136
00:05:51.143 --> 00:05:54.438
So. this is. um... it's about your dad.

137
00:05:54.521 --> 00:05:55.981
[Wyatt sighs]

138
00:05:57.232 --> 00:06:00.736
You remember that nose job
I did on... you know?

139
00:06:00.819 --> 00:06:02.446
[gasps] Oh. of course.

140
00:06:03.113 --> 00:06:04.448
It didn't set.

141
00:06:05.032 --> 00:06:06.492
What do you mean. it didn't set?

142
00:06:06.575 --> 00:06:07.910
Um...

143
00:06:08.911 --> 00:06:10.829
-It kind of...
-[grunts softly]

144
00:06:10.913 --> 00:06:13.457
Dad. that's social suicide.

145
00:06:13.540 --> 00:06:16.001
I know. She had to drop out
of her next movie. It's a mess.

146
00:06:16.085 --> 00:06:18.295
And word's starting to spread
that it's my fault.

147
00:06:18.378 --> 00:06:20.547
-there might be a lawsuit--
-So. so...

148
00:06:20.631 --> 00:06:24.718
we are gonna have
to lay low for a little bit.

149
00:06:25.803 --> 00:06:27.554
Of course.

150
00:06:27.638 --> 00:06:29.348
I didn't know you were
carrying all of this. Dad.

151
00:06:29.431 --> 00:06:30.974
Oh. I'm so glad you feel that way.

152
00:06:31.058 --> 00:06:32.935
because I've had to look for other work.

153
00:06:33.018 --> 00:06:35.521
People in smaller markets
that need someone with my background.

154
00:06:35.604 --> 00:06:37.606
That's exactly what you should be doing.

155
00:06:37.689 --> 00:06:39.108
Way to be proactive.

156
00:06:40.317 --> 00:06:41.652
I found a place.

157
00:06:41.735 --> 00:06:43.946
Uh. it's a private practice.
Only one other doctor.

158
00:06:44.029 --> 00:06:46.240
I can't afford to be choosy right now.

159
00:06:46.323 --> 00:06:48.117
That's great. What's it called?

160
00:06:50.452 --> 00:06:52.204
-Seattle's Elite.
-[clears throat]

161
00:06:53.580 --> 00:06:55.332
Because the other doctor's from Seattle?

162
00:06:55.415 --> 00:06:57.084
Because the practice is in Seattle.

163
00:06:57.167 --> 00:06:58.210
And they're opening an office here?

164
00:06:58.293 --> 00:07:00.462
-No. the office is in Seattle.
-And you'll commute to Seattle--

165
00:07:00.546 --> 00:07:02.256
Elle. we're moving to Seattle.

166
00:07:02.339 --> 00:07:03.882
[chuckles]

167
00:07:03.966 --> 00:07:05.384
No.

168
00:07:07.177 --> 00:07:08.345
It doesn't sound right.

169
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:11.140
Just until people forget
about this whole situation.

170
00:07:11.223 --> 00:07:12.891
How long will that be?

171
00:07:12.975 --> 00:07:14.935
Couple years.

172
00:07:15.018 --> 00:07:16.436
[exhales] That's my whole life.

173
00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:18.438
Hey. Hey.

174
00:07:18.522 --> 00:07:21.733
-The Woods family is adaptable.
-[chuckles]

175
00:07:21.817 --> 00:07:24.361
-Mm-hmm.
-Do you remember when those coyotes

176
00:07:24.444 --> 00:07:27.489
wandered over during
my Night Before the Night Before Party?

177
00:07:27.573 --> 00:07:29.116
-Yes.
-I told everyone.

178
00:07:29.199 --> 00:07:30.701
"Uh. we imported them for ambiance."

179
00:07:30.784 --> 00:07:33.579
And guess what? We all had a great time.

180
00:07:33.662 --> 00:07:35.831
-[crying] We did.
-This is just like that.

181
00:07:37.124 --> 00:07:38.250
Except for longer.

182
00:07:38.333 --> 00:07:39.668
[crying]

183
00:07:42.087 --> 00:07:44.298
[crying. squealing]

184
00:07:51.430 --> 00:07:53.265
[exhales]

185
00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:55.100
[crying]

186
00:07:55.184 --> 00:07:57.019
[gentle music playing]

187
00:07:58.020 --> 00:07:59.271
-[sighs]
-[Madison] Hey.

188
00:07:59.354 --> 00:08:02.024
It's nothing a little
grief shopping can't fix.

189
00:08:02.107 --> 00:08:04.067
Okay. okay. Here's what you have to do.

190
00:08:04.151 --> 00:08:05.485
You know your dad feels guilty. right?

191
00:08:05.569 --> 00:08:06.904
-Yeah. yeah.
-So. you prey on that guilt.

192
00:08:06.987 --> 00:08:08.280
and then you lock it away.

193
00:08:08.363 --> 00:08:09.865
And then you start
to collect interest on it

194
00:08:09.948 --> 00:08:11.700
until one day you need something from him.

195
00:08:11.783 --> 00:08:13.327
-and he owes you big-time.
-Mm-hmm.

196
00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:14.745
-Wh... that works?
-Oh. yeah.

197
00:08:14.828 --> 00:08:16.788
My dad forgot my birthday.
like. five years ago.

198
00:08:16.872 --> 00:08:19.458
and now I can have boys over
with the door closed.

199
00:08:19.541 --> 00:08:21.210
But that doesn't help me now.

200
00:08:21.293 --> 00:08:23.128
I still have to move to...

201
00:08:24.630 --> 00:08:26.840
I can't even say it.

202
00:08:26.924 --> 00:08:28.383
Seattle.

203
00:08:28.467 --> 00:08:29.885
-Aww.
-Hey. we'll talk all the time.

204
00:08:29.968 --> 00:08:31.178
And we'll come visit you.

205
00:08:31.261 --> 00:08:32.763
I've never been to Seattle.

206
00:08:32.846 --> 00:08:34.223
It sounds...

207
00:08:34.306 --> 00:08:35.557
-North.
-Yeah?

208
00:08:35.641 --> 00:08:37.142
-Yeah.
-Your life is not over.

209
00:08:37.226 --> 00:08:38.894
It's just different.

210
00:08:38.977 --> 00:08:40.103
-Mm-hmm.
-Mm-hmm.

211
00:08:40.187 --> 00:08:41.313
-Mm-hmm.
-Oh.

212
00:08:42.940 --> 00:08:44.858
-Elle.
-I'm coming.

213
00:08:45.359 --> 00:08:47.778
[Eva] Honey. the movers are almost here.

214
00:08:49.613 --> 00:08:53.075
I see where all my Ferrero Rocher went.

215
00:08:53.158 --> 00:08:54.910
[Elle] I'm not leaving. [grunts]

216
00:08:54.993 --> 00:08:56.078
Elle. [sighs]

217
00:08:57.079 --> 00:08:59.539
[Elle] I'm faking my own death.

218
00:08:59.623 --> 00:09:02.042
-Look how dead I look.
-[Eva] That's too bad.

219
00:09:02.125 --> 00:09:05.462
I had a gift for you.
but I guess I'll have to give it

220
00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:07.297
to someone who's alive.

221
00:09:08.757 --> 00:09:10.676
Does it rhyme with "Mersace"?

222
00:09:10.759 --> 00:09:12.678
Even better.

223
00:09:12.761 --> 00:09:13.971
[whimpers softly]

224
00:09:16.390 --> 00:09:17.849
[barking]

225
00:09:17.933 --> 00:09:18.850
[gasps]

226
00:09:18.934 --> 00:09:20.560
Oh. my God!

227
00:09:20.644 --> 00:09:22.729
-Oh. is he mine?
-He's yours.

228
00:09:22.813 --> 00:09:24.147
-Oh!
-Ah!

229
00:09:24.231 --> 00:09:25.357
-[laughs]
-I know.

230
00:09:25.440 --> 00:09:27.401
He's so cute.

231
00:09:27.484 --> 00:09:28.944
-[whimpers]
-[gasps]

232
00:09:29.027 --> 00:09:30.445
Aww... Wait.

233
00:09:31.822 --> 00:09:35.742
Did you adopt or did you shop?

234
00:09:36.535 --> 00:09:38.078
The Spellings just redecorated.

235
00:09:38.161 --> 00:09:40.289
and earth tones
don't match their new color palette.

236
00:09:40.372 --> 00:09:45.294
so I rescued
this little blondie from them.

237
00:09:45.377 --> 00:09:47.212
Aww.

238
00:09:47.296 --> 00:09:49.589
My God. you are just a baby.

239
00:09:49.673 --> 00:09:52.592
[gasps] I bet you're a Gemini like me.

240
00:09:52.676 --> 00:09:55.721
-[barks]
-Oh! And such a tough guy.

241
00:09:55.804 --> 00:09:57.889
-[low growl]
-Oh. you need a tough guy name.

242
00:09:58.974 --> 00:10:00.684
I know.

243
00:10:00.767 --> 00:10:02.686
Bruiser.

244
00:10:02.769 --> 00:10:03.979
[chuckles]

245
00:10:05.272 --> 00:10:06.857
[both laugh]

246
00:10:06.940 --> 00:10:09.776
[gentle music playing]

247
00:10:09.860 --> 00:10:11.528
-I am gonna miss her.
-Of course.

248
00:10:11.611 --> 00:10:16.033
Honey. you'll talk every single day
on the phone. Like you do now.

249
00:10:16.116 --> 00:10:18.035
-We can do this.
-[trunk closes]

250
00:10:18.118 --> 00:10:19.119
[Madison] Get in here.

251
00:10:20.203 --> 00:10:21.455
[laughs] Oh. my God.

252
00:10:21.538 --> 00:10:23.081
[gasps] Who is this?

253
00:10:23.165 --> 00:10:24.875
-This is Bruiser.
-[gasps]

254
00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:27.169
